# I. Install Required Tools

## Install Java (JDK 11 or higher)
1. Download JDK from Oracle or OpenJDK.
2. Install to: C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-XX
3. Set environment variables:
   JAVA_HOME = C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-XX
   Add %JAVA_HOME%\bin to PATH
4. Verify:
   java -version

## Install Apache Maven
1. Download and extract Maven.
2. Set environment variables:
   MAVEN_HOME = C:\apache-maven
   Add %MAVEN_HOME%\bin to PATH
3. Verify:
   mvn -version

## Install Visual Studio Code
1. Download and install VS Code.
2. Install Extensions:
   - Extension Pack for Java
   - Maven for Java
   - Debugger for Java

# II. Create Maven Project in VS Code
1. Open VS Code.
2. Press Ctrl + Shift + P.
3. Type: Java: Create Java Project.
4. Select: Maven create from archetype.
5. Choose archetype: maven-archetype-quickstart.
6. Enter details:
   Group Id: com.example
   Artifact Id: demo
7. Choose folder → Project will be created automatically.
8. Push project to GitHub:
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit"
   git branch -M main
   git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/docker_demo.git
   git push -u origin main

# III. CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
1. In local project folder, create:
   .github/workflows/maven.yml

2. Folder structure:
   demo/
   └── .github/workflows/maven.yml

3. Add content to maven.yml:

   name: Java CI/CD Pipeline
   on:
     push:
       branches: [ "main" ]
   jobs:
     build:
       runs-on: windows-latest
       env:
         FORCE_JAVASCRIPT_ACTIONS_TO_NODE24: true
       steps:
       - uses: actions/checkout@v4
       - uses: actions/setup-java@v4
         with:
           distribution: 'temurin'
           java-version: '11'
       - name: Build using Maven
         run: mvn clean install
         working-directory: demo

4. Push changes to GitHub:
   git add .
   git commit -m "Add GitHub Actions workflow"
   git push

# IV. Verify CI/CD
1. Go to your GitHub repository.
2. Open the "Actions" tab.
3. Check pipeline runs for build status.
